RXS signal is field-independent. This\nsupports a previously suggested scenario in which incommensurate charge and\nspin orders compete against each other, in addition to individually competing\nagainst. We discuss the relationship of these results to stripe order 214, the\npseudogap phenomenon, superconducting fluctuations, and quantum oscillations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 Jun 2014 06:30:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 28 Jul 2014 08:14:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-08-27"}
