 a stellar wind model, where the mass-loss rate and collimation (opening\nangle) of the wind are variable. The changes of the opening angle may be\ninduced by small variability in magetization of the inner disc wind. The\nmass-loss rate is found to vary within (6-11)x10^{-8} Msun/yr, with the\naccretion rate of 2.0x10^{-6} Msun/yr.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 Jun 2014 12:29:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 19 Jun 2014 16:21:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
